Question: Problem in accessing elements from google HashMultimap: :I am using below code to get & process value from google HashMultimap    HashMultimap hmm = new HashMultimap();    HashMultimap hmm2 = new HashMultimap();    Element ele;:    hmm2.put("name","Amit");    hmm.put("Amit",ele);    hmm.put("rohit",hmm2); :       Iterator itr =  hmm.keys().iterator();    String ky = (String) itr.next();    System.out.println(hmm.get(ky));    ky = (String) itr.next();    System.out.println(hmm.get(ky));In above code, if map element(or entry) is Element type then i want to do some operation. If it is HashMultimap type then do some other operation. How can i check and pass the object to another function.
Please using this api: Iterator.next.
Answer: <<<api>>>: Iterator.next
<<<code>>>: String ky = (String) itr.next();
<<<explanation>>>: This line of code is used to get the next element from the iterator. The next element is returned and the cursor of the iterator is moved to the next element.

In your case, you are iterating over the keys of the HashMultimap. Each key is a String. You can use the Iterator.next() method to get the next key.

To check if the value associated with the key is of type Element or HashMultimap, you can use the instanceof operator. The instanceof operator is used to test if the object is an instance of the specified type.

Here is how you can modify your code:

```java
Iterator itr = hmm.keys().iterator();
while (itr.hasNext()) {
    String ky = (String) itr.next();
    Object value = hmm.get(ky);
    if (value instanceof Element) {
        // do some operation with Element
        processElement((Element) value);
    } else if (value instanceof HashMultimap) {
        // do some operation with HashMultimap
        processHashMultimap((HashMultimap) value);
    }
}
```

In this code, the processElement() and processHashMultimap() are methods that you need to define to perform the operations you want to perform on the Element and HashMultimap objects, respectively.
